metadata.description: Maya Long Count ↔ Western date correlations. For each sourced Maya LC from Mesoweb's 'Table of Palenque Rulers' (Modified GMT 584285, Gregorian), this file includes computed western dates for several common correlation constants (584283–584286) in both proleptic Gregorian and proleptic Julian calendars.

mesoweb_palenque_rulers_table.title: Table of Palenque Rulers
mesoweb_palenque_rulers_table.author: Joel Skidmore
mesoweb_palenque_rulers_table.notes: Modern dates in the table are Gregorian and correlated using Modified GMT 584285 (as stated on the page).

fields.event: born|acceded|died (as indicated in the source table)
fields.calendar_round: Calendar Round text from the source table
fields.correlation_jdn: Julian Day Number assigned to 0.0.0.0.0 under the given correlation constant
fields.western_date: ISO-8601 date in the specified calendar (astronomical year numbering for BCE)
fields.direct_in_source: true only for (correlation_jdn=584285, western_calendar=gregorian) which is explicitly given by the source
fields.source_western_date: the source's Gregorian date (ISO) when direct_in_source=true, else null
